                                                                   GZIP 

   
	1. To compress any file-  gzip filename
	
 2.    To decompress any file-  gunzip filename.txt.gz
                     Dir-       gzip -d filename.txt.gz

 3.    To see the stats of any file-  gzip -l filename.txt.gz

 4.    To compress any file with a compression rate-  gzip -9 filename.txt

 5.     To see the content of file while decompress-  gunzip -c filename.gz

 6.     To see the content of any file-  zcat filename.gz


                                                                  BZIP2

	7.   To compress any file-  bzip2 filename.txt

 8.     To decompress any file-  bunzip2 filename.txt.bz2

 9.     To see the data of any file-  bzcat filename.txt.bz2

 10.   Recover data from damaged file-  bzip2recover filename.txt.bz2

                                                          ARCHIVING AND BACKUP

  11.   To archieve-  tar cvf dir.tar dir

  12.   To see the content of archieve dir-   tar tvf dir.tar

  13.   To unbundle the archieve directory-  tar xvf dir.tar

  14.   To compress and bundle any folder-  tar cvfz dir.tgz dir1
                                            tar cvfj dir.tar.bz2 dir1

  15.   To remove compression and bundling of any folder-   tar -xvf dir.tar.bz2


                                                         ZIP  AND  UNZIP

  16.  To install zip and unzip-  yum install zip and unzip

  17.   To zip any directory-  zip -r abc directoryname/

  18.   To see the content of any directory-  unzip -l abc.zip

  19.  To unzip any file at any location-  unzip abc.zip -d dir2/

  20.  To delete any file from any zipped folder-  zip -d abc.zip *.mp3   

  21.  To update any zipped folder-  zip -u abc.zip dir/*.mp3
